HEADWORD: Clingstone
<hw>Cling"stone`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Having the flesh
attached closely to the stone, as in some kinds of peaches.</def> --
<def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>A fruit, as a peach, whose flesh adheres to the
stone.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Clingy</ent>⟦br⟧
